What is the result?

discussion.content:
There is no right answer here.

Variables that form the object's state are
int a = 0;
int b = 0;
int c = 0;
The problem is with policy for managing concurrent access to the object's state.
Concurrent access to it can be done within the package directly.
Reads and writes are atomic for reference variables and for most primitive variables (all types except long and double).
So, there is the guarantee that it is atomic, but with no guarantees about the visibility of the (potentially) new value from other threads.

